PN,41403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1773668266
OL,3,CWhat are the symptoms of meningitis
OL,4,Cand what is the advice for students
OL,6,FSepticaemia can also cause a
OL,7,Fcharacteristic rash that does not fade
OL,8,Fwhen pressed against a glass.
OL,10,FThe UK Health Security Agency says
OL,11,Fstudents can sometimes overlook these
OL,12,Fsigns, as they may be similar to a
OL,13,Fhangover.
OL,15,FTrish Mannes, UKHSA regional deputy
OL,16,Fdirector for the South East, said:
OL,17,F"Students are particularly at risk of
OL,18,Fmissing the early warning signs of
OL,19,Fmeningitis because they can be easily
OL,20,Fconfused with other illnesses such as
OL,21,Fa bad cold, flu, or even a hangover.
OL,26,@yD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
